  "text": "The Java class loading delegation chain in OpenJDK (sg-evals/jdk--742e735d) involves the following key files:\n\n1. **src/java.base/share/classes/java/lang/ClassLoader.java** — Defines the abstract `ClassLoader` class and the core `loadClass(String name, boolean resolve)` method (lines 534–570) that implements the parent-first delegation model. The method: (a) checks if the class is already loaded via `findLoadedClass(name)`; (b) delegates to the parent loader (`parent.loadClass(name, false)`) or the bootstrap loader (`findBootstrapClassOrNull(name)`) if parent is null; (c) only if not found, calls `findClass(name)` on the current loader. This is the canonical parent-delegation algorithm.\n\n2. **src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/BuiltinClassLoader.java** — Defines `BuiltinClassLoader extends SecureClassLoader`, the common base class for the three built-in loaders (boot, platform, application). It overrides `loadClass` with module-aware logic: it first checks the module system to find which `BuiltinClassLoader` owns the package, then delegates directly to that loader or falls back to parent delegation via `parent.loadClassOrNull(cn)`. Key method: `loadClass(String cn, boolean resolve)`.\n\n3. **src/java.base/share/classes/jdk/internal/loader/ClassLoaders.java** — Defines the `ClassLoaders` utility class that creates and wires together the three built-in class loaders in a static initializer: `BootClassLoader` (extends `BuiltinClassLoader`, represents the bootstrap loader), `PlatformClassLoader` (extends `BuiltinClassLoader`, parent = `BOOT_LOADER`), and `AppClassLoader` (extends `BuiltinClassLoader`, parent = `PLATFORM_LOADER`). This establishes the delegation chain: App → Platform → Boot.\n\n4. **src/hotspot/share/classfile/classLoader.cpp** — The HotSpot C++ implementation of the native `ClassLoader`. Implements `ClassLoader::initialize()`, `classLoader_init1()`, `classLoader_init2()`, and the low-level classpath/module image scanning used by the bootstrap loader to locate and load `.class` files from the JRT image and classpath entries. This is the native side that backs the Java `ClassLoader` native methods.\n\n5. **src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.hpp** and **src/hotspot/share/classfile/systemDictionary.cpp** — Define the `SystemDictionary` C++ class (an `AllStatic` utility class) that serves as the VM-level cache for all loaded classes. Key methods include `resolve_or_fail()`, `resolve_or_null()`, `find_instance_klass()`, and `find_instance_or_array_klass()`. The dictionary maps (class name, class loader) pairs to `InstanceKlass*` objects, preventing duplicate loading and enforcing loader constraints. The `.cpp` file implements `get_system_class_loader_impl()`, `do_unloading()`, and the `load_instance_class` path that calls back into Java's `ClassLoader.loadClass()`."
}

